{
  "texts": [
    "On average 42 of the top 100 atoms were correctly predicted (Fig. 5).",
    "As shown in Fig. 5d, the model can predict the atoms in the protein pocket that are mostly flexible during the MD run (large spheres), and detect the more rigid protein regions (small spheres).",
    "This allows a fast Resource https://doi.org/10.1038/s43588-024-00627-2 examination of the protein pocket without the necessity of a lengthy MD setup and simulation.",
    "The adaptability model gives an innovative example of how experimental structures can be enhanced from the MD-based MISATO data.",
    "A binding affinity AI model combines MISATO MD and QM data."
  ]
}